Data Friends

Alex Wang, Sam Choi, Amanda(Yanqian) Wu

5/7/2017

A Statistical Analysis of the Subprime Mortgage Crisis

Key questions
- 1. was it possible to predict the subprime mortgage crisis? If so, what were the identifiable signals that preceded the crisis?
- 2. What were the effects of the subprime mortgage crisis on the overall economy? Additionally, how did it affect industries outside of the housing sector?
- 3. What can we infer from the relationship between different securities and statistics?

Data Source
Yahoo Finance (https://finance.yahoo.com/lookup)
Bloomberg (accessed via Bloomberg’s private software application)
U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development
U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics
Chicago Board Options Exchange
Economic Research, Federal Reserve Bank of St. Louis

Methods
In class: data wrangling, ggplot, regex, data structures Outside class: time series
